# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  VPNjantit OpenVPN config template
#
#  SETUP (do this on the AWS server):
#
#  1. Go to https://www.vpnjantit.com  → Login / Register (free)
#  2. Go to "Create Account" → choose OpenVPN
#  3. Select country: Qatar (QA) if available, otherwise UAE (AE)
#     — UAE IPs can reach the Qatar MOI portal
#  4. Download the .ovpn config file
#  5. Copy it to this directory as  server.ovpn:
#        scp -i fees2-mumbai.pem your-config.ovpn ubuntu@<EC2-IP>:~/qatar/vpn/server.ovpn
#  6. Set credentials in the project root .env (NOT committed to git):
#        echo "OPENVPN_USER=your_username"   >> ~/qatar/.env
#        echo "OPENVPN_PASSWORD=your_password" >> ~/qatar/.env
#  7. If your .ovpn file has an inline  <auth-user-pass>  block,
#     remove it — gluetun injects credentials via env vars.
#
#  IMPORTANT: server.ovpn is gitignored (contains server address + port).
#             Never commit it.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Paste the contents of your downloaded .ovpn file below this line,
# or replace this entire file with the downloaded config.

client
dev tun
proto udp
remote qa1.vpnjantit.com 1194
resolv-retry infinite
nobind
persist-key
persist-tun
remote-cert-tls server
cipher AES-256-CBC
verb 3
# auth-user-pass   ← remove this line; gluetun handles credentials
